        <div class="section">
            <h2>World Mechanics</h2>
            <p>Magic is categorized into:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Physical Magic:</strong> Enhances physical abilities but leads to exhaustion.</li>
                <li><strong>Arcane Magic:</strong> Draws from nature/emotions and requires innate talent.</li>
                <li><strong>Pious Magic:</strong> Comes from divine favor and can be revoked.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The city's economy follows a standardized coin system (cp, sp, gp, pp) with heavy reliance on trade.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Port Dunwyd: Factions & Governance</h2>
            <p>The city is ruled by a rotating <strong>Council of Five</strong>, each faction controlling a different aspect of governance:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Sentinel Authority:</strong> Military and law enforcement.</li>
                <li><strong>Trade Consortium:</strong> Merchant interests, currently in power.</li>
                <li><strong>Obsidian Veil:</strong> Arcanum, controlling knowledge and suppressing religion.</li>
                <li><strong>Gilded Dominion:</strong> Aristocracy and wealth.</li>
                <li><strong>Artisan Assembly:</strong> Craftsmen and industry.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Each faction has its own hierarchy, internal conflicts, and hidden agendas, making political maneuvering a key element of the game.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Ye Ol' Fiddle Tavern</h2>
            <p>A quiet retreat for laborers near the Barge Load Area.</p>
            <h3>Key Characters:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Corbin Duskwood:</strong> Gruff owner, dislikes most patrons but takes a liking to adventurers.</li>
                <li><strong>Elias "Strings" Marrow:</strong> Fiddle player, knows rumors but speaks little.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Services:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Food & Drink:</strong> Bitter Ale, River Rum, Fish Stew.</li>
                <li><strong>Lodging:</strong> Shared common rooms, small private rooms, and long-term quarters.</li>
                <li><strong>Stables:</strong> Basic horse lodging.</li>
